 Republican National Chairman <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Atwater </PERSON> let fly some barbs of his own following a roast by <ORGANIZATION> South </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Carolina </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republicans </ORGANIZATION>. `` Mama always told me do n't attack unarmed people _ especially in a battle of wits,'' he told the more than 1,000 people at Saturday night's event. <PERSON> Atwater </PERSON> also poked fun at himself. He said he was glad to be back in <LOCATION> Charleston </LOCATION>, noting he spent the first five years of his life there. `` I learned from <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> that the more places you call home, the more votes you get,'' he said. Gov. <PERSON> Carroll </PERSON> <PERSON> Campbell </PERSON> said, `` I often wondered what <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> would be when he grew up. I'm still wondering.''
