 It was a convention that seemed stranger than fiction. The Tacoma Sheraton was invaded by 1,500 science fiction fans for Norwescon XI, a convention that featured a masquerade ball, seminars on the physical properties of alien worlds, chain mail fabrication and Star Trek. The activities turned the heads of hotel guests not attending the convention. On one stairway, a starfighter and a Venusian princess brushed by two businessmen, while nearby a barbarian adjusted his battle gear. `` What is this?'' one businessman asked the other. The conference ended Sunday.
