<DATELINE>VALDEZ, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A crewman without proper certification was in command when an Exxon tanker apparently hit two rocks and ran aground, causing the nation's biggest oil spill, the company said. Officials said a third mate was in command, against company policy, at the time of Friday morning's accident that sent an estimated 10.1 million gallons of crude oil into <LOCATION> Prince </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Williams </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sound </LOCATION> south of here and prompted the governor Sunday to declare the sound a disaster area. The Exxon Valdez crewman did not have the proper license to legally operate such a large ship in the sound, officials said. <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shipping </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Dunphy </PERSON> said Sunday that the captain, <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Hazelwood </PERSON>, was in the cabin at the time of the grounding. But today he said `` the captain's whereabouts are uncertain throughout the entire incident. It is known he was not on the bridge for the complete time.'' Both he and another company spokesman, <PERSON> Sharon </PERSON> <PERSON> Curran-Wescott </PERSON>, said that even if <PERSON> Hazelwood </PERSON> was present during part of the time on the bridge, he was not in command. `` We do know the captain was not in command,'' Ms. <PERSON> Curran-Wescott </PERSON> said. `` He apparently may have been physically present on the bridge.'' <PERSON> Dunphy </PERSON> said <PERSON> Hazelwood </PERSON> was consulting an attorney. Meanwhile, winds topping 25 knots this morning forced postponement of efforts to clean up the sound with chemicals to disperse the oil or fire to burn it off. `` Some of the cleanup operations, such as the use of skimmers and also dispersants and the burn technique, have been put on hold,'' <PERSON> Dunphy </PERSON> said. He said he was unsure if the weather would improve enough to allow cleanup to begin later in the day