in <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>. `` My husband would like to see his mother before she dies,'' <PERSON> Hilda </PERSON> <PERSON> Aybar </PERSON> said while waiting in front of the agency. `` I do n't see why he should n't go. Threats phoned to Marazul and other agencies criticize them for indirectly supporting <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> by providing hard currency to <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>, and more broadly by softening attitudes toward the communist government. The latest bombing came three days after another <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> agency announced the first direct mail to <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>, and two weeks after the Kiwanis Club of <LOCATION> Little </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Havana </LOCATION>, which sponsored <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>'s Calle Ocho street party, caused a controversy by banning any singers who had performed in <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>.
