ernment officials and journalists, but the boom soon may give way to a bust. `` I would n't expect people in <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> will want to see beautfiful Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON> with oil floating in it,'' <PERSON> Leland </PERSON> said. `` It's a negative we'll probably live with all summer long,'' said <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Scott </PERSON>, owner of <ORGANIZATION> Alaska </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Glacier </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tours </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Anchorage </LOCATION>, which coordinates cruises in Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON>. `` Any time something negative happens, that's what people remember. They do n't remember that it's cleaned up.'' -- -
