<HEAD>$Adv00</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Anytime</HEAD>
<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>At the Movies: ``Rooftops,'' ``SING''</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: ``SING'' opens March 31.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` Rooftops'' Let's hear it for the septuagenarian film director. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Crichton </PERSON>, who made `` The Lavender Hill Mob'' and other comedy classics, scored an Academy Award nomination at 78 for his rollicking `` A Fish Named <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON>.'' <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Fuller </PERSON> -LRB- `` Pickup on South Street'' -RRB- is starting another action movie at 77. Now <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Wise </PERSON>, 74, has a new film, `` Rooftops.'' It's not in the range of Wise's `` West Side Story,'' to which it is inevitably compared. But `` Rooftops'' is handsomely produced, directed with kinetic energy and skillfully acted by a youthful cast. Amazingly, `` Rooftops'' was produced on the streets and of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> for $ 8 million. Wise's last movie, `` Star Trek: The Motion Picture,'' reportedly cost $ 50 million. Like `` West Side Story,'' `` Rooftops'' deals with urban warfare. The setting is <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION>'s lower <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Side </LOCATION>, where homeless teen-agers live on top of abandoned tenements and earn a meager living by scrounging used plumbing and auto parts. They are at odds with punk gangs and, on a more sinister level, the venomous drug dealers. A straight-arrow loner known only as T -LRB- <PERSON> Jason </PERSON> <PERSON> Gedrick </PERSON> -RRB- pumps iron at his watertower apartment and tries to stay out of trouble. Then he falls for <PERSON> Elena </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Troy </PERSON> <PERSON> Beyer </PERSON> -RRB-, a virtuous girl who has been trapped into serving as lookout for her drug-dealing cousin, <PERSON> Lobo </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Velez </PERSON> -RRB-. Conflict builds to a violent showdown, with T and a few allies mismatched against <PERSON> Lobo </PERSON> and his thugs. While not a musical per se, `` Rooftops'' is scored to contin