<HEAD>Shamrock Holdings Abandons Bitter Takeover Bid for Polaroid</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DANA KENNEDY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Shamrock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> abandoned its eight-month-old struggle to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Monday, less than a week after a <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> court dealt the company a fatal blow in its attempt to gain control of the instant photography giant Polaroid officials said they entered into an agreement with <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON> under which <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON> would terminate its $ 3.2 billion tender offer and proxy contest and both sides would end litigation resulting from the Shamrock bid. <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON>, based in <LOCATION> Burbank </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, and its affiliate companies also agreed not to attempt to gain control of Polaroid for at least 10 years. Shamrock, which offered $ 45 a share for <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> stock, was stymied Thursday by a <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> court decision clearing the way for <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> to repurchase 16 million shares at a premium price of $ 50 each. `` We are disappointed and frustrated by the <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> courts,'' <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON> president <PERSON> Stanley </PERSON> <PERSON> Gold </PERSON> said Monday. `` It's certainly not good news for folks who are trying to do what we did.'' Some analysts said the <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> ruling allowing the <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> purchase could signal a new era in the kinds of defensive strategies planned by takeover targets. `` Up until now, attacking companies have been able to peel away layer by layer of companies' defenses,'' said <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Fernandez </PERSON>, managing director of <ORGANIZATION> Brean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Murray </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securi