<HEAD>Japan's Major Bank-Credit Card May Deal in U.S. Through BofA</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: Dwane is cq</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> is negotiating with <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s largest bank card company for the exclusive right to honor the JCB credit card at more than 100,000 outlets in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, bank officials announced Monday `` This historic agreement would allow Japanese tourists and business travelers visiting the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to use their most popular credit card throughout our extensive merchant base,'' said <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Fontana </PERSON>, senior vice president in charge of merchant services at the San Francisco-based bank. Bank of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> says it can perform all sales and servicing of <ORGANIZATION> JCB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> card accounts through its existing credit card programs and will bill merchants for <ORGANIZATION> JCB </ORGANIZATION> use through <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> statements Under the deal, no other bank can honor the <ORGANIZATION> JCB </ORGANIZATION> card in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. JCB's six sponsoring Japanese banks, which are not prohibited from setting up their own servicing programs with <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> merchants, currently have no such programs. Through independent arrangements, JCB is accepted at about 20,000 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> businesses, most of them on the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> and in <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION>. `` This deal will greatly expand the utility of our card for our holder dramatically, both for visitors and Japanese nationals now living or working in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>,'' said <ORGANIZATION> JCB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dwane </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Krumme </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Fontana </PERSON> indicated <ORGANIZATION> BofA </ORGANIZATION>'s move is the first step toward expanding merchants' ability to accept various bank cards without having to arrange service programs with each sponsoring company. `` We feel this will be a significant step in providing merchants with a convenient, consolidated service for different card types,'' said <PERSON> Fontana </PERSON>. JCB is <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s largest bank-related credit card issuer and has a card base of more than 13 million and a merchant network of more than 1 million establishments worldwide. The JCB card currently is accepted in 102 countries and territories, although most of the company's business remains limited to <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Fontana </PERSON> said the agreement is expected to be signed within 90 days and would apply to 60,000 businesses with 100,000 outlets nationwide. If approved, <ORGANIZATION> BofA </ORGANIZATION> will be the first major overseas partner of JCB.
